items.title: Anthropic rolls out Claude AI for finance, integrates with Excel to rival Microsoft Copilot
items.summary: San Francisco-based AI startup Anthropic is making its most aggressive push yet into the trillion-dollar financial services industry . Anthropic embeds its Claude AI assistant directly into Excel, connecting it to real-time market data . The move marks a significant escalation in Anthropic's campaign to position itself as the AI platform of choice for banks and asset managers .

items.title: From human clicks to machine intent: Preparing the web for agentic AI
items.summary: As AI-driven agents begin to browse on our behalf, the web is being exposed as fragile . The web was designed for human consumption, not for machine execution . The architecture that works so well for people is a poor fit for machines . The contrast between humans and machines in how to fix the web becomes sharper in enterprise applications, authors say .
